ports = [22, 2222, 3389, 443, 8022, 22222]

for port in ports:
    sock = socket.socket\(socket.AF_INET, socket.SOCK_STREAM\)
    sock.settimeout\(3\)
    result = sock.connect_ex\(\(host, port\)\)

    print\(f''Port {port}: {status}''\)
    sock.close\(\)

import socket

host = ''144.124.252.23''
ports = [22, 2222, 443]

for port in ports:
    print\(f''\\n=== Port {port} ===''\)
    try:
        sock = socket.socket\(socket.AF_INET, socket.SOCK_STREAM\)
        sock.settimeout\(5\)
        sock.connect\(\(host, port\)\)
        # Try to receive banner
        sock.settimeout\(3\)
        try:
            data = sock.recv\(1024\)
            print\(f''Banner: {data[:200]}''\)
        except socket.timeout:
            print\(''No banner received \(timeout\)''\)
        sock.close\(\)
    except Exception as e:
        print\(f''Error: {e}''\)
")
